places.name: Eiffel Rive Gauche
places.description: The Eiffel Rive gauche hotel welcomes you in one of the most prestigious districts of Paris, at the heart of the triangle Eiffel Tower, Invalids, Champs-Elysees ... Near the Trocadero, near the Champs de Mars, the Arc of Triumph, of Concorde, of the museum of the Quai Branly, Unesco ... Tourism, shopping, affairs, entertainment ... You will be just a few steps away from the high places of the heritage, the most beautiful places of interest, the shops selling luxury goods, the theaters, and the business area. In a quiet street of this restless left riverside, nested in a former convent, our hotel is an island of peace in the cosy and elegant atmosphere. Let charm by his sober and sophisticated atypical frame, its unique atmosphere, take time to stroll in our patio ... And savor the pleasure to relax you in this harbor of peace in the middle of the city lights.

address_obj.address_string: 6 rue du Gros Caillou 07 Arr., 75007 Paris France

places.name: Hotel Le Cercle - Tour Eiffel
places.description: Hôtel Le Cercle - Tour Eiffel ★★★ , completely renovated in 2020, offers you a warm welcome to the seventh arrondissement of Paris, one of the Capital's liveliest residential neighborhoods. The Eiffel Tower and the Champ de Mars are just steps away, and the École Militaire lies before you. Located in the prestigious avenue de la Bourdonnais, Le Cercle retains the intimacy and poetry of a Parisian home. In its chic and contemporary decor, our elegant hotel invites you to unwind in the refinement of typical Parisian houses. Located adjacent to the Eiffel Tower, the Champ de Mars, and the École Militaire, the Hôtel Le Cercle E boasts an ideal location from which to explore Paris. Countless must-see tourist attractions await, just minutes away on foot or by public transportation (from the École Militaire Métro/bus station): the Hôtel des Invalides, the Trocadéro Esplanade, the Alexandre III bridge, the Grand Palais, the Champs-Élysées shopping district and the Arc de Triomphe, the neighborhood of Saint-Germain-des-Prés, the Rodin Museum, the Quai Branly Museum, the Musée d'Orsay, the Garnier Opera House, the Montparnasse Tower, the Louvre… Right next to the Hotel Le Cercle, the Rue Cler offers you the opportunity to immerse yourself in the daily life of the neighborhood and its residents. This famous street is a favorite destination of true Parisian gourmets. On this lively, traditional, pedestrian street, you'll find exceptional food purveyors, many cafés and restaurants, wine merchants, delicatessens, master chocolatiers and pastry chefs, and more.

address_obj.address_string: 117 avenue de la Bourdonnais, 75007 Paris France

placeDetails.name: Hotel Lancaster Paris Champs-elysees
placeDetails.description: À deux pas des Champs-Élysées et de l’Arc de Triomphe, l’Hôtel Lancaster révèle l’art de vivre à la française. Cet établissement historique possède une vaste et précieuse collection d’œuvres d’art alliée subtilement à des éléments contemporains. Cette adresse, nichée dans le 8e arrondissement de Paris, offre à ses clients un confort et un raffinement inégalés. Le restaurant Monsieur Lancaster et le bar CopperBay Lancaster vous accueillent pour un déjeuner ou un dîner gastronomique mettant à l'honneur une cuisine française de saison sous la direction du chef Sébastien Giroud. Un agréable patio constitue un écrin de sérénité au cœur de la capitale. Laissez vous porter par le charme authentique et élégant de l'hôtel Lancaster Paris.

placeDetails.name: Chateau Des Fleurs
placeDetails.description: Le Château des Fleurs est un boutique-hôtel situé tout à côté des Champs Elysées et du Triangle d'Or. Imaginé par Quintana Partners, il rend hommage à l'esprit parisien de la Belle Epoque et propose 37 chambres, certaines avec une vue sur les Champs Elysées, certaines communicantes, d'autres sur deux niveaux. Les salons ont été imaginés pour offrir un cadre intime à la décoration unique aux Parisiens comme aux voyageurs lointains qui souhaitent s'y détendre, prendre un verre au bar ou déjeuner et dîner en dégustant la cuisine coréenne authentique et généreuse de la Cheffe Ji-Hye Park, créatrice d'OMA. Côté détente, le spa by Omnisens, propose cabines de soins simples et double, fitness, bassin et sauna.

placeDetails.name: Fraser Suites Le Claridge Champs-Elysees
placeDetails.description: Le Claridge Champs-Elysées, built in 1914 right on the Champs-Elysées Avenue, has been witness to a century of political and romantic history of France. Secrets kept forever behind the walls of this legendary palace which has welcomed so many stars. A century later, Le Claridge Champs Elysées and its facade became listed French historical monuments, entering into the world of the most beautiful hotel residences in the world. The renovation changed this historical establishment into a contemporary, elegant Parisian residence. Spacious and comfortable, the110 Suites and apartments offer an exceptional view of the Champs Elysées Avenue or the peaceful patio of the residence. The blend of black and beige in the wall-to-wall carpeting evoke the black and white checkered pattern of the Parisian townhouses and the play of blue bands painted on the walls creates a unique ambiance. Wild silk curtains, velvet chairs, wool rugs and leather bring back the luxury of Claridge’s past glory. This is a new era for the Claridge Champs Elysées which, in 2006, joined the prestigious Fraser Suites collection.

address_obj.address_string: 74 Avenue des Champs Elysees, 75008 Paris France

placeDetails.name: Hotel California
placeDetails.description: Built in 1925, this Haussmanian style building has been the favourite luxury hotel of the American press and Hollywood Stars. More than just a hotel, this is an authentic art gallery for all art lovers with its private collection of over 3000 oils and lithographs. With its fine sense of luxury, this 4 star hotel has been turned into a fine family mansion just a step away from the Champs Elysees and belongs to Les Hotels du Roy group.

placeDetails.name: Cristal Champs Elysees
placeDetails.description: Just a stone’s throw from one of the most beautiful streets in the world and yet in a calm setting you will find the Champs-Elysées Cristal Hotel.An undisturbed location, like a secret treasure, located on Rue Washington, 50meters from the Champs Elysees and which is a new-found area for luxury shopping in a prestigious district. The hotel is ideally located for professional or tourist activities.

placeDetails.name: citizenM Paris Champs-Elysees
placeDetails.description: Picasso, Hemingway, Fitzgerald – there's a reason artists have always flocked to Paris. It's the city of love, of lights, and now another citizenM. Our fourth Parisian hotel stands on the world's most luxurious street – Champs-Élysées. ​Unlike the usual high prices and la-di-da hospitality you find on the avenue, citizenM gives you affordable luxury in a prime location. When you arrive at our can't-miss hotel, there's no long queue at reception. Self-check-in takes only a minute at our kiosks – or use our app to check-in before you arrive. The second-floor living room is packed with art, books and oh-so-comfy Vitra furniture. Feeling peckish? Slide over to canteenM – it's open 24/7 and expands onto an amazing outdoor terrace with bistro-style furniture and chic loungers. There's an intimate, awning-covered courtyard for all-weather dining. The 8th-floor cloudM bar serves shaken and stirred cocktails with a side of Eiffel Tower views. At the front is a terrace overlooking the iconic Champs-Élysées. At the back, an expansive hideout and lusciously green inner courtyard. Is this a place to dine, date or party? We think so! Our hot & cold breakfast buffet comes with unique local treats, familiar favorites, and healthy options for everyone — including vegans and vegetarians. Pile your plate with warm pastries, scrambled eggs, fresh fruit, and more.

placeDetails.name: Hotel Vernet
placeDetails.description:
Welcome to Hotel Vernet, your Paris “home away from home.” Hotel Vernet aims to make your visit as relaxing and enjoyable as possible, which is why so many guests continue to come back year after year.
Close to some of Paris' most popular landmarks, such as Louvre Museum (1.9 mi) and Montmartre (2.1 mi), Hotel Vernet is a great destination for tourists.
As your “home away from home,” the hotel rooms offer a flat screen TV, air conditioning, and a minibar, and getting online is easy, with free wifi available.
Guests have access to room service and a concierge while staying at Hotel Vernet. In addition, Hotel Vernet offers breakfast, which will help make your Paris trip additionally gratifying.
If you like seafood restaurants, Hotel Vernet is conveniently located near Le Jules Verne, Pedra Alta, and Le Grand Colbert.
If you’re looking for something to do, Eiffel Tower (1.0 mi), Arc de Triomphe (0.2 mi), and Champs-Elysees (0.5 mi) are a nice way to spend some time, and they are all within walking distance of Hotel Vernet.
Hotel Vernet puts the best of Paris at your fingertips, making your stay both relaxing and enjoyable.
